SIMPLE: exulcerate
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Exulcerate
<hw>Ex*ul"cer*ate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t. & i.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>exulceratus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>exulcerare</ets> to make sore;
<ets>ex</ets> out + <ets>ulcerare</ets>. See <er>Ulcerate</er>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>To ulcerate.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> ⟦ldquo⟧To
<xex>exulcerate</xex> the lungs.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Evelyn.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To corrode; to fret; to chafe; to inflame.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Minds <qex>exulcerated</qex> in themselves.</q>
<rj><qau>Hooker.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Exulcerate</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Exulcerate
<hw>Ex*ul"cer*ate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>exulceratus</ets>, p. p.]</ety> <def>Very sore; ulcerated.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Bacon.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Exulceration</ent>⟦br⟧
